-- Brazil’s Sudene Approves $234 Million for Northeast Wind Farms
-- B y   S t e p h a n   N i e l s e n
-- 2013-05-21T14:34:25Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-05-21/brazil-s-sudene-approves-234-million-for-northeast-wind-farms.html
Brazil  agreed to provide 478.7
million reais ($234 million) in funding for wind farms in the
country’s northeast.  Superintendencia do Desenvolvimento do Nordeste , the
regional development agency, approved 299.3 million reais for a
complex of five wind projects known as Faisa in the northeastern
state of Ceara, Brazil’s official gazette said today on its
 website . The Faisa projects total 136.5 megawatts of capacity
and will use turbines supplied by India’s  Suzlon Energy Ltd. (SUEL)   Sudene, as the agency is known, also approved 125.4 million
reais for three wind projects under development by Spain’s Corp.
Gestamp SL and 54 million reais for Eolica Pedra do Reino SA.  The investment will be furnished by Fundo de
Desenvolvimento do Nordeste, a fund managed by Sudene, according
to the statement, which didn’t say whether the funding will
comprise equity or debt.  To contact the reporter on this story:
